**Truncated Description:** SCP-4639 was an incorporeal force that possessed Site-322 Researcher John Azniok on December 11, 2016. SCP-4639 claimed to be the mythological Kraken in search of "a worthy vessel." It was capable of speech through the form it possessed.

Immediately after possession, a number of growths appeared on Azniok's form, resembling black and purple tentacles. Within 20 hours, Azniok was enveloped in these growths. Despite this, Azniok appeared to have the entity under control for a time. This was a fruitless endeavor, as seven days later, Azniok was slowly overtaken by SCP-4639.

[[/div]]
[[div class="description"]]
= [[size 110%]]__**SCP-001 Influenced Containment Failures**__[[/size]]

For a sentient/sapient humanoid anomaly, a number of protocols needed to be fulfilled before full containment could be enacted. At the time, Director Lague was also floating the idea of what is today known as the [[[/integration-program-hub | Integration Program]]]. As such, SCP-4639 was deemed a candidate for a beta test of the working methods. Below are truncated transcripts from the discussions between Site-322 staff and SCP-4639:

[[div class="coll"]]
[[collapsible show="+ Open Transcript +" hide="+ Close Transcript +"]]
[[<]]
[[div class="interview"]]
= **TRANSCRIPT**
-----
= **<<BEGIN LOG>>**

**Coix:** Am I speaking to John or...

**SCP-4639:** It's John right now.

**Coix:** Okay, great. How have you been dealing with these sudden changes?

**SCP-4639:** It's awful. I can't see and I keep tripping over myself. The dude in my head keeps asking me to drown myself--

**SCP-4639:** WE ARE A SEA BEAST. MANY LEGGED. HORRIBLE, FRIGHTENING, BLASPHEMOUS!

**SCP-4639:** I'm a pasty, 130-pound white dude, you cocksucker.

**SCP-4639:** I HAVE NEVER SUCKED A CHICKEN, BOY. DENYING YOUR DESTINY WILL ONLY FULFILL IT QUICKER.

**SCP-4639:** Fuck you.

**SCP-4639:** FUCKING ME IS FUCKING YOURSELF.

**Coix:** Are we okay?

**SCP-4639:** No! This is fucking traumatizing.

**SCP-4639:** YOU ARE WHINING LIKE A SMALL, BABY, PUNY, GIRL. WE ARE A THING OF MYTH. HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THE PICTURES OF ME? WE WILL LOOK GOOD AND RIGHT HORRIFIC, I PROMISE.

**SCP-4639:** Get out of my head!

**SCP-4639:** WE NEED TO GO TO THE OCEAN.

**SCP-4639:** I don't //want// to!

**SCP-4639:** WHO WOULDN'T WANT TO BE A SQUID? YOU, GOOD SIR, WOULD YOU LIKE TO BE A SQUID?

**Coix:** No, I wouldn't want to be a squid.

**SCP-4639:** MMMMMM. YOU'VE NEVER WANTED TO WRAP YOUR MANY WIGGLY ARMS AROUND THE RAGGED UNDERBELLY OF A DELECTABLE SHIP, TEARING IT APART PLANK BY PLANK AS THE MELODY OF MILLIONS OF SCREAMING SEAMEN BOUNCE ACROSS THE WAVES?

**Coix:** Can I talk to--

**SCP-4639:** YOU'VE NEVER WANTED TO SWIM SO VERY FAR DOWN INTO THE BRINY DEPTHS OF THE GREAT BLUE SEA, GOING WHERE NO MAN, WOMAN, OR YUMMY CHILD EVER HAS? THE FEELING OF BILLIONS OF TONS OF PRESSURE ON YOUR BACK AS YOU SEE THE CREATURES OF THE DEPTHS IS INDESCRIBABLE--

**Coix:** No! I don't want to be a squid and neither does John!

**SCP-4639:** THEN YOU ARE A CAT!

**Coix:** Huh?

**SCP-4639:** OF THE PUSSY VARIETY.

= **<<END LOG>>**
[[/div]]
[[/<]]
[[/div]]
[[/collapsible]]

[[div class="testfile"]]
= **__INCIDENT ID: 001.5-01__**
[[div class="testvideo"]]
**SCP-001 Effect:** SCP-4639 was initially held in a standard humanoid containment chamber, as it was believed a majority of Azniok's anatomy was intact. This was proven to be false, as SCP-4639 managed to escape through a gap between the door and the floor. It was quickly recaptured and sedated. An examination of SCP-4639 found that the human form of Azniok had been converted into the mantle and fins seen on squids.
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="testfile"]]
= **__INCIDENT ID: 001.5-02__**
[[div class="testvideo"]]
**SCP-001 Effect:** Tropical storm localized solely on Site-322 formed. It rained a number of objects, ranging from seawater to living sea life such as sharks, penguins, and squids. SCP-4639 claimed this was "patronage."
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="testfile"]]
= **__INCIDENT ID: 001.5-03__**
[[div class="testvideo"]]
**SCP-001 Effect:** As time progressed, SCP-4639 gained a number of anomalous capabilities. These included:
* Highly-effective manipulation tactics;
* The ability to summon raging storms;
* Control of sea life;
* Limited omnipotence.

SCP-4639 utilized a combination of these abilities to escape Foundation containment.

[[div class="interview"]]
= **TRANSCRIPT**
-----
= **<<BEGIN LOG>>**

**SCP-4639:** I AM THE GOD OF THE SEA.

**Coix:** You sure are, bud.

**SCP-4639:** RELEASE ME.

**Coix:** No.

**SCP-4639:** YOU WANT TO LET ME GO IN THE OCEAN.

**Coix:** You know what? Now that I think about it...

**SCP-4639:** REALLY?

**Coix:** No.

**SCP-4639:** YOU WANT TO LET ME OUT SO BAD.

**Coix:** I bet. Will you shut--

**SCP-4639:** I AM THE GOD OF THE SEA. HARK, MORTAL.

**Coix:** You are the god of the sea.

**SCP-4639:** YOU WANT TO LET ME OUT SO BAD. HARK.

**Coix:** I want to let you out so bad.

= **<<END LOG>>**
[[/div]]

SCP-4639 used the above phrasing on all Foundation personnel who attempted to prevent its escape. Recontainment efforts were initiated following this incident.

The entity was quickly tracked due to its "shedding" a number of tentacles as it made its escape. This trail led to Site-322's docking area, where the corpse of SCP-4639 was discovered. The cause of death was deemed to be asphyxiation due to drowning.

Post-mortem dissections found that while a majority of Azniok's external anatomy was converted, his internal organs were still in the process of transforming from human into squid.

[[/div]]
